{
  "texts": [
    "Readers interested in further practical advice on implementing DDSP techniques for audio synthesis should refer to the accompanying web book, available at https://intro2ddsp.github.io/.",
    "A causal linear time-invariant (LTI) filter with impulse response h(t) is said to have an infinite impulse response (IIR) if there does not exist a time T such that h(t) = 0 for all t > T. In the case of digital filters, this property arises when the filter's difference equation includes a nonzero coefficient for a previous output.",
    "We present the dominant methods for differentiable IIR filtering in Table 2.",
    "Optimising IIR filter coefficients by gradient descent is not a new topic.",
    "Several algorithms for adaptive IIR filtering and online system identification rely on the computation of exact or approximate gradients (Shynk, 1989)."
  ]
}